    "Then, the embedding is processed by a stack of encoders consisting of a multi-head attention mechanism and a feedforward network, where each of these sub-layers is connected by a residual connection and normalized by layer normalization.",
    "The information is then passed to the decoder, which has a similar architecture with two multi-head-attention layers and a feed-forward network.",
    "Finally, linearization and softmax activation are applied to the output before it is produced as the final result (Vaswani et al. 2017; Lin et al. 2022).",
    "Finally, GNNs take a graph representation as input.",
    "In a graph, the data can be represented as global context, nodes, edges, and the connectivity of the graph."
